[1] Colombia (Sucre department): ex Venezuela
Date: Fri 20 Apr 2018 00:07 AM COT
Source: BLU Radio Nacional [in Spanish, trans. & edited Mod.JG]
https://www.bluradio.com/salud/casos-de-sarampion-siguen-en-aumento-ya-son-11-confirmados-176008-ie430


The number of cases of measles in Colombia has climbed up to 11 in the past few hours, after 2 new cases were confirmed in San Onofre municipality, Sucre department

The affected persons are a 16-year old adolescent and a 4-year old girl who came from Venezuela a few days ago.

These patients will be examined until next May [2018], and healthcare authorities are currently running the appropriate protocol for taking care of this situation and they aim to determine whether there may be some more persons affected because of contact with these cases.

We have to remember that Colombia was declared a measles-free country (native cases) since 2015, but because of the health crisis due to lack of vaccines and drugs in its neighboring country (Venezuela), the virus came back.

The Colombian National Institute of Health (INS, according to its Spanish initials) has ruled out more than 1000 (suspicious) cases, but every week the number of infected persons is increasing.

Also, the recently reported cases show there is transmission occurring in young persons and in adults, which makes management more difficult, since as age increases, more complications may supervene.

There is also another case in San Onofre, a 22-year-old young man who is currently being treated. The Colombian government has emphasized that it is predictable that the numbers of cases may increase as long as in Venezuelan children are not vaccinated at an adequate age, which is between 8 and 15 months old, with a booster dose between 4 and 6 years of age.

[Byline: Santiago Ángel]

