[8] Connecticut (New Haven county)
Date: Tue 24 Apr 2018 12:43 PM EDT
Source: WTNH [edited]
http://www.wtnh.com/news/connecticut/new-haven/dph-2-confirmed-cases-of-measles-in-new-haven-county/1137705051


The Connecticut Department of Health (DPH) has confirmed 2 cases of measles in New Haven County on [Tue 24 Apr 2018]. The DPH reports that the 2 infected people are children under 12 months of age who reside in the same household and traveled internationally. Both babies acquired their infection outside of the country.

The DPH says that they are working to identify contacts and implement control measures. They were able to confirm that any exposures happened in New Haven County between 11 and 17 Apr 2018.

While measles is a highly contagious disease, the majority of people exposed are not at risk since most people have been vaccinated or have had measles in the past. "The single best way to protect yourself and your children from measles is to be vaccinated. While most people have had the measles vaccination, it's important to know your vaccination status and to be aware of the signs and symptoms of measles so you can get medical attention," said DPH Commissioner Dr Raul Pino in a press release.

[Byline: Alex Ceneviva]

