[9] Iowa (Des Moines): alert
Date: Mon 23 Apr 2018 4:00 PM CT
Source: Des Moines Register [edited]
https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/health/2018/04/23/measles-warning-issued-patrons-des-moines-ankeny-restaurants/543792002/


Patrons of 2 chain restaurants in the Des Moines metro may have been exposed to measles, the Iowa Department of Public Health [IDPH] is warning.

The restaurants were visited by a confirmed measles patient from Missouri. Anyone who was at the same location was exposed to the highly contagious disease -- and needs to contact their doctor if they begin to show symptoms, the Iowa Department of Public Health says. [See the source URL above for a list of restaurants potentially contaminated by measles virus.]

"Since it is too late to prevent these exposed people from coming down with measles, they could become ill and start spreading the disease any day now," said IDPH Medical Director, Dr Patricia Quinlisk, in a news release. "That is why is it so important that anyone who has not received two doses of measles vaccine go in and get vaccinated today. That way if they are exposed in the next month or so when they go about their normal activities, they will be protected."

Kansas has had 18 confirmed cases of measles in several counties since 8 Mar 2018. Those cases have been traced back to a day care.

Missouri now has 4 confirmed cases of measles, all out of the Kansas City area.

The last confirmed case of measles in Iowa was in 2011.

In 2015, the United States experienced a large, multi-state measles outbreak linked to Disneyland in California.

[Byline: Kim Norvell]

